<div>
<h2 style="font-size:150%">ROYAL STUDIOS CELEBRATES SIXTY SOULFUL YEARS at the ORPHEUM in MEMPHIS</h2>

<ul>
<li><strong>Saturday, November 18th, 2017</strong></li>
<li><strong>Orpheum Theatre, 203 S Main St, Memphis, TN 38103</strong></li>
<li><strong>For more information go to <a href="http://royalstudios.com/" title="Royal Studios" style="color:blue;a:hover:background:white;">Royal Studios</a></strong><a href="http://royalstudios.com/" title="Royal Studios"></a></li>
</ul>
<p>Come join the celebration! I'm thrilled to be honoring my father's legacy as one of the original Royal Studios / Hi Records recording artists. Dad was always very proud of the work he did while on the Hi Record label. He had enormous respect for the groundbreaking soulful sounds created by some of the world's finest musicians and producers over at Royal Studios. Sounds that continue to set the bar today with acts like <strong>Bruno Mars</strong>, winner of the <a href="http://royalstudios.com/uptown-funk-wins-2016-grammy-record-of-the-year/" title="2016 Grammy Award Winning Record of the Year, "Uptown Funk", by Bruno Mars" style="color:blue;a:hover:background:white;"><strong>2016 Grammy Award Record of the Year, &quot;Uptown Funk&quot;.</strong></a>  </p>
<p>Performances By: <strong>Anthony Hamilton, Boz Scaggs, Robert Cray, Dee Dee Bridgewater, William Bell, Syl Johnson, Dave Stewart from the Eurythmics , and Tony Joe White. Super Producer &amp; Drummer Steve Jordan will be music director along with Hi Rhythm and the Royal Horns.</strong></p>
<p><a href="https://orpheum-memphis.com/event/royal-studios-60th-anniversary" title="Royal Studios"><img style="float:left; margin:13px;" src="images/royal-studios-60th.jpg" width="269" height="240" alt="Royal Studios 60th Anniversary at the Orpheum in Memphis"></a></p>
<p>As the final event of the Royal Studios’ 60th Anniversary series, Sixty Soulful Years takes a look at the past, present and future of Royal with incredible performing acts. Celebrating the recent collaborations and Grammy wins of Boo Mitchell, Sixty Soulful Years will be an unbelievable night of music, dance, film and fun.</p>
</div>





